
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "# Wine Quality Prediction (Classification) — White Wine\n",
    "\n",
    "## Objective\n",
    "Predict white wine quality category from physicochemical properties using classification models.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Design Decisions (Instructor-aligned)\n",
    "- Regroup quality into 3 classes:\n",
    "  - Low (≤5), Medium (=6), High (≥7)\n",
    "- White wine is analysed **separately** from red wine because its chemical distributions differ.\n",
    "- Compare **at least three models**:\n",
    "  - GaussianNB (probabilistic baseline)\n",
    "  - Logistic Regression (linear baseline)\n",
    "  - Random Forest (nonlinear ensemble)\n",
    "- Metrics are chosen based on imbalance and classification goals:\n",
    "  - **macro-F1** as primary metric (fair across classes)\n",
    "  - accuracy as secondary reference\n",
    "\n",
    "## Improvements Implemented in Coding\n",
    "- EDA (data exploration) and feature analysis\n",
    "- Missing & duplicate checks (duplicates removed if any)\n",
    "- Feature correlation analysis (feature–feature and feature–quality)\n",
    "- Outlier-robust scaling (RobustScaler) for scale-sensitive models\n",
    "- Class weighting for imbalance handling\n",
    "- Stratified 5-fold cross-validation (mean ± std)\n",
    "- GridSearchCV tuning (macro-F1 objective)\n",
    "- Overfitting analysis (train vs test + CV train vs valid)\n",
    "- Deeper error analysis (raw + normalized confusion matrix + top confusions)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "id": "bY4_wJIUxsEJ"
   }
  },
  {
