  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "## EDA: Class Distribution (Imbalance)\n",
    "\n",
    "White wine typically exhibits a different imbalance pattern from red wine.\n",
    "The Medium-quality class often dominates, while High-quality remains a minority.\n",
    "\n",
    "This motivates:\n",
    "- **macro-F1** as the primary metric (class-balanced evaluation)\n",
    "- **class_weight** in training to reduce majority-class bias"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "id": "0zo9AyZjburM"
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "source": [
    "counts = df[\"quality_label\"].value_counts()\npct = df[\"quality_label\"].value_counts(normalize=True) * 100\n\ndisplay(pd.DataFrame({\"count\": counts, \"percent(%)\": pct.round(2)}))\n\nplt.figure()\nplt.bar(counts.index, counts.values)\nplt.title(\"Class Distribution (White Wine)\")\nplt.ylabel(\"Count\")\nplt.show()\n"
