    "## Discussion (White Wine)\n",
    "\n",
    "- The class distribution is typically dominated by the Medium category, motivating macro-F1 and class weighting.\n",
    "- RobustScaler is used for Logistic Regression due to skewness/outliers in several features.\n",
    "- Random Forest generally performs well because it captures nonlinear relationships among chemical properties.\n",
    "- Error patterns concentrate around neighbouring classes, indicating overlapping chemical profiles and subjective scoring.\n",
    "- Overfitting is assessed using train–test gaps and CV train–validation gaps; the tuned parameter grid includes regularisation (min_samples_leaf) to improve generalisation."
